<p>Ahola! I've been lurking for a few years now and didn't really think about making an account until today. What drove me to do it was a godawful article that's so bad I wanted to downvote it. It was something about cardboard box man-spiders. Crazy, huh? Can't find it now but it's been marked for deletion, which is appropriate. I even had a couple ideas to improve on it but I'm still not familiar with the rules on rewriting deleted articles though.</p>
<p>I'm just going to be a casual reader/reviewer for now but if I ever get to writing an article/tale, I'll be in your care!</p>
<p>I usually drop dead the moment I go to bed except that one time when I finished reading a novel. It was still ongoing so I spent some time theorizing what would happen next until I finally fell asleep. Also, if that wasn't obvious enough, I'm fond of reading light novels so I'm probably going to Tales more.</p>

